commit_list.message:
Rename POST /entries/create to POST /entries/new. URIs should preferably not have any verbs in
them. We're creating a new entry, so we're POSTing to the resource /entries/new, which represents
"a new entry".
commit_list.repo_description: (Experimental and outdated.) A blog, powered by Sinatra (http://sinatrarb.com/). An experiment.

commit_list.message:
Revert the previous revision:
> To prevent confusion, use a different URL for each action. Using the same URL with different
> HTTP methods could become a bit confusing.
Using verbs like "edit" or "delete" is not really RESTful, a URI should refer to a resource, and
http://example.com/entries/:slug/delete is not a resource.

This reverts commit 3bc4f5585c0d409fca781a08d2d5eb2f0d917642.
